{
  "narration": "Kira gives a crisp nod, her eyes narrowing as she nocks an arrow and melts into the deeper shadow of the ruined entryway. \"You take point, Eirik. If the wolves charge, I'll make my shots count. Just keep your shield high and trust my aim.\"\n\nThe crumbling stones of the Forgotten Waystation loom around you, their battered arches and mossy blocks forming a maze of half-fallen halls. Your boots crunch softly on grit and old leaves as you raise your shield, mace at the ready. The air is tense, thick with the scent of cold ash and something feral--the unmistakable musk of wolves, close and hungry.\n\nFrom within the collapsed main chamber, you hear a deep, guttural growl. Two gaunt, gray wolves slink from behind an overturned wagon, hackles raised and yellow eyes fixed on you. One bares its fangs in challenge while the other circles wide, seeking an opening.\n\nKira whispers from cover, \"I've got the one on the right. Hold steady!\"\n\nThe wolves tense, preparing to lunge. The ruined walls and scattered debris offer little cover, but your stance is firm and your shield gleams in the filtered light.\n\nSteel yourself, Eirik--the wolves are moments from attacking. The air crackles with imminent danger as you ready your defense and Kira draws a careful bead.\n\nCombat is about to begin.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "createEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "player": "eirik_hearthwise",
        "npcs": ["Scout Kira"],
        "monsters": ["Wolf", "Wolf"],
        "encounterSummary": "Two hungry wolves emerge from the rubble of the Forgotten Waystation, circling to attack Eirik and Kira as they search for Sila's stolen chest."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 5
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "As the echoes of battle fade, the ruins of the Forgotten Waystation return to tense silence. The bodies of the two wolves lie sprawled amidst mossy stones and scattered debris, their threat ended by your determined teamwork. Kira lets out a relieved breath, lowering her bow with a tight, proud smile. \"That was too close, Eirik. You held the line like a true shield-brother. Come here, let's check your wounds.\"\n\nBlood trickles down your forearm where one of the wolves' fangs found flesh; exhaustion tugs at your limbs, your breath ragged. Kira kneels beside you, deftly binding your wound with strips of cloth from her pack. \"You'll have a fine scar, but you need real rest before we press on.\"\n\nShe glances around the ruined clearing, her gaze sharp and searching. \"The bandits can't have gone far. Their tracks are fresh, and I smell lamp oil and burnt powder--signs they hid something here. Let's search for Sila's iron-banded chest and any clues about Malarok's plans. Keep your shield near, just in case.\"\n\nEirik, you feel battered but not beaten, driven by purpose and the hope of helping Sila and the outpost. Would you like to search the ruins now, tend to your wounds further, or take a short rest to recover your strength? Time is precious, but pushing on while injured carries its own risks.",
